[
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843157",
        "quote": "One of the lesser-known ways of making new words is to form a blend - and a blend is when you run two words together to make a third word.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843157"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            },
            {
                "name": "Blend",
                "url": "/topics/blend"
            },
            {
                "name": "Making",
                "url": "/topics/making"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843159",
        "quote": "You don't usually get a compound word where the first part is a slang thing and the second part is a rather ordinary or formal thing - they don't usually mix - but 'gobsmacked' is a perfect exception to that rule.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843159"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Perfect",
                "url": "/topics/perfect"
            },
            {
                "name": "Exception",
                "url": "/topics/exception"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rather",
                "url": "/topics/rather"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843161",
        "quote": "One notable feature is that English doesn't have much of a system for expressing relative social status.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843161"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "System",
                "url": "/topics/system"
            },
            {
                "name": "Social",
                "url": "/topics/social"
            },
            {
                "name": "Feature",
                "url": "/topics/feature"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843163",
        "quote": "Every usage, no matter how bizarre or nonstandard, fascinates me, as it tells me something about the way language is evolving.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843163"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Bizarre",
                "url": "/topics/bizarre"
            },
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            },
            {
                "name": "Usage",
                "url": "/topics/usage"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843164",
        "quote": "The death of a language. The word has the same kind of reluctant resonance as it has when we talk about the death of a person. And indeed, that's how it should be. For that's how it is. A language dies only when the last person who speaks it dies.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843164"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Death",
                "url": "/topics/death"
            },
            {
                "name": "Last",
                "url": "/topics/last"
            },
            {
                "name": "Kind",
                "url": "/topics/kind"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843165",
        "quote": "It doesn't take a language long to disappear once the spirit to continue with it leaves its community. In fact, the speed of the decline has been one of the main findings of recent linguistic research.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843165"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Spirit",
                "url": "/topics/spirit"
            },
            {
                "name": "Fact",
                "url": "/topics/fact"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843166",
        "quote": "A community, once it realises that its language is in danger, can get its act together and introduce measures which can genuinely revitalise. You've seen it happen in Australia with several Aboriginal languages. And it's happening in other countries, too.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843166"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            },
            {
                "name": "Genuinely",
                "url": "/topics/genuinely"
            },
            {
                "name": "Several",
                "url": "/topics/several"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843172",
        "quote": "How do you spell the name of the Irish prime minister? It sounds like 'teeshuck', but we spell it 'taoiseach.' We respect foreign spellings these days - a sign of our more egalitarian times, perhaps.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843172"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Minister",
                "url": "/topics/minister"
            },
            {
                "name": "Prime",
                "url": "/topics/prime"
            },
            {
                "name": "Spell",
                "url": "/topics/spell"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843170",
        "quote": "There is no such thing as an ugly accent, like there's no such thing as an ugly flower.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843170"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Ugly",
                "url": "/topics/ugly"
            },
            {
                "name": "Like",
                "url": "/topics/like"
            },
            {
                "name": "Thing",
                "url": "/topics/thing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513688",
        "quote": "Vocabulary is a matter of word-building as well as word-using.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513688"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Matter",
                "url": "/topics/matter"
            },
            {
                "name": "Vocabulary",
                "url": "/topics/vocabulary"
            },
            {
                "name": "Well",
                "url": "/topics/well"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843177",
        "quote": "There's an old little jingle: 'The chief use of slang is to show that you're one of the gang.' What that means is that every social group has its own linguistic bonding mechanism. If there's a group of lawyers, they have their own slang. If there's a group of doctors, they have their own slang, and so on.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843177"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Lawyers",
                "url": "/topics/lawyers"
            },
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            },
            {
                "name": "Use",
                "url": "/topics/use"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513684",
        "quote": "Language has no independent existence apart from the people who use it. It is not an end in itself; it is a means to an end of understanding who you are and what society is like.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513684"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Independent",
                "url": "/topics/independent"
            },
            {
                "name": "Like",
                "url": "/topics/like"
            },
            {
                "name": "Means",
                "url": "/topics/means"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843175",
        "quote": "The Internet has given us 10 or 15 new styles of communication: long messages like blogging, and then short messages like texting and tweeting. I see it all as part of an expanding array of linguistic possibilities.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843175"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Possibilities",
                "url": "/topics/possibilities"
            },
            {
                "name": "Expanding",
                "url": "/topics/expanding"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843149",
        "quote": "The Internet offers endangered languages a chance to have a public voice in a way that would not have been possible before.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843149"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Voice",
                "url": "/topics/voice"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Offers",
                "url": "/topics/offers"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513676",
        "quote": "The story of English spelling is the story of thousands of people - some well-known, most totally unknown - who left a permanent linguistic fingerprint on our orthography.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513676"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Spelling",
                "url": "/topics/spelling"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Well-Known",
                "url": "/topics/well-known"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843148",
        "quote": "The main effect of the Internet on language has been to increase the expressive richness of language, providing the language with a new set of communicative dimensions that haven't existed in the past.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843148"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            },
            {
                "name": "In The Past",
                "url": "/topics/in_the_past"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843158",
        "quote": "You can say now, 'I dissed him' - to diss, I dissed him - or, 'Stop dissing her'. And that's the interesting thing, that it's the prefix that's become the verb! It's a most remarkable development.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843158"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Interesting",
                "url": "/topics/interesting"
            },
            {
                "name": "Development",
                "url": "/topics/development"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843176",
        "quote": "It's very difficult to find even one or two criteria that you will find in every Internet situation, and the reason is that the technology constrains language in individual ways.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843176"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Reason",
                "url": "/topics/reason"
            },
            {
                "name": "Individual",
                "url": "/topics/individual"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843139",
        "quote": "Increasingly, over the past ten years, I've come to take the view that a cultural perspective is intrinsic to the future of language teaching and learning, especially in the case of English, as it becomes increasingly global.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843139"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Past",
                "url": "/topics/past"
            },
            {
                "name": "Over",
                "url": "/topics/over"
            },
            {
                "name": "Increasingly",
                "url": "/topics/increasingly"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513673",
        "quote": "Texting has added a new dimension to language use, but its long-term impact is negligible. It is not a disaster.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513673"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            },
            {
                "name": "Use",
                "url": "/topics/use"
            },
            {
                "name": "Added",
                "url": "/topics/added"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843151",
        "quote": "Language itself changes slowly, but the Internet has speeded up the process of those changes so you notice them more quickly.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843151"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Process",
                "url": "/topics/process"
            },
            {
                "name": "More",
                "url": "/topics/more"
            },
            {
                "name": "Quickly",
                "url": "/topics/quickly"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513681",
        "quote": "English has been this vacuum cleaner of a language, because of its history meeting up with the Romans and then the Danes, the Vikings and then the French and then the Renaissance with all the Latin and Greek and Hebrew in the background.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513681"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Romans",
                "url": "/topics/romans"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Greek",
                "url": "/topics/greek"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513685",
        "quote": "At any one time language is a kaleidoscope of styles, genres and dialects.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513685"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Kaleidoscope",
                "url": "/topics/kaleidoscope"
            },
            {
                "name": "Genres",
                "url": "/topics/genres"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513672",
        "quote": "Ever since the arrival of printing - thought to be the invention of the devil because it would put false opinions into people's minds - people have been arguing that new technology would have disastrous consequences for language.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513672"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Thought",
                "url": "/topics/thought"
            },
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843143",
        "quote": "Bilingualism lets you have your cake and eat it. The new language opens the doors to the best jobs in society; the old language allows you to keep your sense of 'who you are.' It preserves your identity. With two languages, you have the best of both worlds.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843143"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Language",
                "url": "/topics/language"
            },
            {
                "name": "Worlds",
                "url": "/topics/worlds"
            },
            {
                "name": "Lets",
                "url": "/topics/lets"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843141",
        "quote": "Languages like English, Spanish, and Chinese are healthy languages. They exist in spoken, written, and signed forms, and they're used by hundreds of millions of people all over the world. But most of the 6,000 or so of the world's languages aren't in such a healthy state.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843141"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Used",
                "url": "/topics/used"
            },
            {
                "name": "Millions Of People",
                "url": "/topics/millions_of_people"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513678",
        "quote": "Likewise, there is no evidence that texting teaches people to spell badly: rather, research shows that those kids who text frequently are more likely to be the most literate and the best spellers, because you have to know how to manipulate language.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513678"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Evidence",
                "url": "/topics/evidence"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rather",
                "url": "/topics/rather"
            },
            {
                "name": "Badly",
                "url": "/topics/badly"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513687",
        "quote": "A feature of English that makes it different compared with all other languages is its global spread.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513687"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            },
            {
                "name": "Languages",
                "url": "/topics/languages"
            },
            {
                "name": "Feature",
                "url": "/topics/feature"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843168",
        "quote": "People are very ready to criticize other people's accents. There's no correlation between accents and intelligence or accents and criminality, but people do make judgments.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843168"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            },
            {
                "name": "Judgments",
                "url": "/topics/judgments"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513674",
        "quote": "Although many texters enjoy breaking linguistic rules, they also know they need to be understood.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513674"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Need",
                "url": "/topics/need"
            },
            {
                "name": "Linguistic",
                "url": "/topics/linguistic"
            },
            {
                "name": "Although",
                "url": "/topics/although"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843167",
        "quote": "Enshrined in a language is the whole of a community's history and a large part of its cultural identity. The world is a mosaic of visions. To lose even one piece of this mosaic is a loss for all of us.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843167"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Part",
                "url": "/topics/part"
            },
            {
                "name": "Large",
                "url": "/topics/large"
            },
            {
                "name": "Enshrined",
                "url": "/topics/enshrined"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513680",
        "quote": "Text messaging is just the most recent focus of people's anxiety; what people are really worried about is a new generation gaining control of what they see as their language.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513680"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Generation",
                "url": "/topics/generation"
            },
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            },
            {
                "name": "Gaining",
                "url": "/topics/gaining"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513683",
        "quote": "Anyone interested in language ends up writing about the sociological issues around it.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513683"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Ends",
                "url": "/topics/ends"
            },
            {
                "name": "Sociological",
                "url": "/topics/sociological"
            },
            {
                "name": "Anyone",
                "url": "/topics/anyone"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843169",
        "quote": "Everybody wants to say who they are and where they're from. And the easiest and cheapest and most universal way of doing that is through their accent.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843169"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Doing",
                "url": "/topics/doing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Everybody",
                "url": "/topics/everybody"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843142",
        "quote": "There's nothing unusual about a single language dying. But what's going on today is extraordinary when we compare the situation to what has happened in the past. We're seeing languages dying out on a massive scale.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843142"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Going",
                "url": "/topics/going"
            },
            {
                "name": "Compare",
                "url": "/topics/compare"
            },
            {
                "name": "In The Past",
                "url": "/topics/in_the_past"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513677",
        "quote": "Spellings are made by people. Dictionaries - eventually - reflect popular choices.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_513677"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Reflect",
                "url": "/topics/reflect"
            },
            {
                "name": "Eventually",
                "url": "/topics/eventually"
            },
            {
                "name": "Made",
                "url": "/topics/made"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843162",
        "quote": "I don't have any particular desire to see words making a comeback. They are of their era, after all, and that is their identity - they form part of the linguistic color of a period.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843162"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Desire",
                "url": "/topics/desire"
            },
            {
                "name": "Making",
                "url": "/topics/making"
            },
            {
                "name": "Period",
                "url": "/topics/period"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843146",
        "quote": "We are rearing a generation of kids who are more equitable and more understanding about the existence of language variety and why it is there.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843146"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Generation",
                "url": "/topics/generation"
            },
            {
                "name": "More",
                "url": "/topics/more"
            },
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843154",
        "quote": "Over the last 50 years or so, we have seen an increasing cultural diversification across the country. Accents are a reflection of society, and as society changes, so accents change.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Crystal",
            "url": "/quotes/david_crystal_843154"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Last",
                "url": "/topics/last"
            },
            {
                "name": "Country",
                "url": "/topics/country"
            },
            {
                "name": "Over",
                "url": "/topics/over"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
